                <h3>Children (4-12 years)</h3>
                <p>
                    • Breakfast: Whole grain cereal with milk, fruits like banana or apple.<br>
                    • Lunch: Rice/roti with vegetables, dal, and a small portion of curd.<br>
                    • Snack: Handful of nuts or fruit yogurt.<br>
                    • Dinner: Light meal with soup, chapati, and vegetables.
                </p>
        
                <h3>Teens (13-19 years)</h3>
                <p>
                    • Breakfast: Eggs, toast, and a fruit smoothie.<br>
                    • Lunch: Whole grain roti or brown rice with protein (paneer, chicken), salad.<br>
                    • Snack: Sprouts or a peanut butter sandwich.<br>
                    • Dinner: Lean protein with veggies and a light carb like quinoa or roti.
                </p>
        
                <h3>Adults (20-59 years)</h3>
                <p>
                    • Breakfast: Oats, chia seeds, and fruit bowl.<br>
                    • Lunch: Balanced meal with complex carbs, lean protein, and mixed vegetables.<br>
                    • Snack: Green tea with roasted chana or fruits.<br>
                    • Dinner: Light meal—grilled vegetables, lentils, and soup.
                </p>
           
                <h3>Seniors (60+ years)</h3>
                <p>
                    • Breakfast: Dalia or soft idlis with milk or herbal tea.<br>
                    • Lunch: Soft-cooked rice with dal, vegetables, and curd.<br>
                    • Snack: Steamed fruits or soaked almonds.<br>
                    • Dinner: Light soup, khichdi, or soft chapatis with veggies.
                </p>
                <img src="images/diet2.jpg" alt="">
